{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_111","type":"agent_message","text":"The cleaner fix is in the generated `akka` test project, not more metadata guessing: native image appears to preserve only one root `reference.conf`, so the Akka actor defaults are getting lost. I’m wiring the test project to materialize Akka’s upstream `reference.conf`/`version.conf` under unique names and include them from a single test-owned `reference.conf`, which should make JVM and native resolve the same config."}}
